## ▶ PHASE 1 PROMPT — Project Setup + Database Schema + Auth
### Use this first. Run it in a fresh Next.js project in Cursor.

I am building AI Commitment OS — a Commitment Intelligence Platform 
that automatically detects and tracks every commitment made across 
meetings, messages, and emails. See .cursorrules for full context.

TASK: Set up the complete project foundation.

─── STEP 1: Initialize the project ───────────────────────────────

Create a new Next.js 14 project with:
- TypeScript (strict mode)
- Tailwind CSS
- App Router
- src/ directory structure

Install all dependencies:
  Core:         next react react-dom typescript
  UI:           tailwindcss shadcn/ui @radix-ui/react-* lucide-react
  Database:     @supabase/supabase-js @supabase/ssr
  State:        zustand
  Data:         @tanstack/react-query
  Forms:        react-hook-form zod @hookform/resolvers
  AI:           @anthropic-ai/sdk openai (for embeddings)
  Email:        resend
  Utilities:    date-fns clsx tailwind-merge
  Dev:          @types/node @types/react eslint prettier

─── STEP 2: Supabase setup ───────────────────────────────────────

Create /lib/supabase/client.ts     → browser Supabase client
Create /lib/supabase/server.ts     → server Supabase client (cookies)
Create /lib/supabase/middleware.ts → auth middleware helper
Create /middleware.ts              → Next.js middleware for session refresh

─── STEP 3: Full database schema ─────────────────────────────────

Create /supabase/migrations/001_initial_schema.sql with the full Phase 1 schema.

─── STEP 4: Environment variables ────────────────────────────────

Create .env.local with:
  NEXT_PUBLIC_SUPABASE_URL=
  NEXT_PUBLIC_SUPABASE_ANON_KEY=
  SUPABASE_SERVICE_ROLE_KEY=
  ANTHROPIC_API_KEY=
  OPENAI_API_KEY=
  RESEND_API_KEY=
  NEXT_PUBLIC_APP_URL=http://localhost:3000
  SLACK_CLIENT_ID=
  SLACK_CLIENT_SECRET=
  SLACK_SIGNING_SECRET=
  ZOOM_CLIENT_ID=
  ZOOM_CLIENT_SECRET=
  ZOOM_VERIFICATION_TOKEN=
  GOOGLE_CLIENT_ID=
  GOOGLE_CLIENT_SECRET=

─── STEP 5: TypeScript types ─────────────────────────────────────

Generate /types/database.ts with full TypeScript types matching 
every table above. Also create /types/index.ts with all app-level 
types (Commitment, Source, Integration, etc.) as documented in 
.cursorrules.

─── STEP 6: Auth flow ─────────────────────────────────────────────

Build complete auth:
- /app/(auth)/login/page.tsx     → email/password + Google OAuth
- /app/(auth)/signup/page.tsx    → signup with workspace creation
- /app/(auth)/callback/page.tsx  → OAuth callback handler
- /app/(auth)/onboarding/page.tsx → 3-step onboarding:
    Step 1: Name your workspace
    Step 2: Connect first integration (Slack, Zoom, or Gmail)
    Step 3: Import or create your first commitment

